Jeanette Chabalala, News24 (iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Kimberley &ndash; A 41-year-old man was arrested for possession of suspected stolen copper cable with an estimated street value of R13 000, Northern Cape police said. &nbsp;The man was arrested following a tip-off that he was storing suspected stolen copper on his farm near Kimberley, said Lieutenant Olebogeng Tawana. &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Tawana said the six bags containing copper weighing 197kg were found hidden in his storeroom.&nbsp;The man was expected to appear in the Kimberley Magistrate's Court on Thursday where he is to face a charge of possession of stolen property.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.